                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-rose-700">Day 6: Troubleshooting & Quality</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 items-center">
                        <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-3">
                            <p>Your first prints won't be perfect. Learning to diagnose and fix problems is a crucial skill for any maker.</p>
                             <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                                <li>Fix bed adhesion, stringing, and layer shifting.</li>
                                <li>Experiment with slicer settings for better quality.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <img src="https://placehold.co/600x400/f43f5e/ffffff?text=Troubleshooting" alt="Troubleshooting 3D Prints" class="rounded-lg object-cover w-full h-full">
